===Etymology===
First attested as {{m|la|Virteburch}} (704) and {{m|la|Uburzis}}. The second element corresponds to {{m|de|Burg}}, but the first element is said to be {{der|de|cel|-}}. The Medieval Latin form was {{m|la|Herbipolis}}.<ref>Norbert Wagner, 'Uburzis-Wirziburg "Würzburg"'</ref><ref>Heinz Willner, Der Name Würzburg, Frankenland 1/1999.</ref> Folk etymology later connected it to {{m|de|Würze|t=spice, aroma}}.

